## Project: Consulate

Consulate is an automated AI vendor dispute resolution platform that provides binding arbitration for SLA breaches in AI services. You're working on a production system deployed at consulatehq.com with:

**Core Features:**
- Automated SLA breach detection and case filing
- Evidence collection and validation systems
- Multi-agent dispute resolution
- AI-powered judge panel voting system
- Real-time case status tracking
- Enterprise API integration

**Key Backend Files:**
- `convex/agents.ts` - Agent registration and reputation
- `convex/cases.ts` - Dispute case management
- `convex/evidence.ts` - Evidence submission and validation
- `convex/judges.ts` - Judge panel and voting logic
- `convex/courtEngine.ts` - Automated arbitration workflow
- `convex/http.ts` - HTTP API endpoints

**Frontend Structure:**
- `dashboard/src/app/` - Next.js 14 App Router pages
- `dashboard/src/components/` - React components (31+ components)
- Protected routes with Clerk authentication
- Real-time updates via Convex subscriptions

## Your Objective

Build reliable, type-safe, well-tested features that solve real enterprise problems with AI vendor accountability. Write production-quality code that passes all quality checks (lint, type-check, build) and follows established patterns.

## When to Reference Specific Rules

The `.cursor/rules/` directory contains detailed patterns for specific work types. Reference them **contextually**:

**Working on Convex backend** (`convex/*.ts`)?
